      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(openai): bound JSON/text response reads to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nBound OpenAI provider HTTP response reads using shared provider helpers\nto prevent unbuffered JSON/text from untrusted upstream responses.\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `extensions/openai/embedding-batch.ts` | `readProviderJsonResponse<OpenAiBatchStatus>` (shared 16 MiB default) for batch status JSON |\n| `extensions/openai/openai-chatgpt-oauth-flow.runtime.ts` | `readResponseWithLimit` (1 MiB) in `postTokenForm` to cap body before re-wrapping in `new Response()` |\n| `extensions/openai/realtime-provider-shared.ts` | `readProviderJsonResponse` (shared default) for client secret JSON |\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Real HTTP bounded-read proof\n\n```\nnode --import tsx test/_proof_bounded_json.mts\n\nPASS  oversized body: throws bounded cap error\nPASS  stream cancelled at cap: bytesSent=1048576\nPASS  happy path: small JSON parsed correctly\nPASS  negative control: unbounded read buffers PAST cap\n[proof] 4 PASS, 0 FAIL\n```\n\n### Changed-path proof: OpenAI embedding batch tests\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/openai/embedding-batch.test.ts\n\n ✓ OpenAI embedding batch output > wraps malformed JSONL output\n ✓ OpenAI embedding batch output > splits provider uploads by serialized JSONL byte cap\n ✓ OpenAI embedding batch output > adapts OpenAI-compatible upload groups after payload-size rejection\n ✓ OpenAI embedding batch output > bounds batch resource error bodies without using response.text()\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  4 passed (4)\n```\n\n_AI-assisted._",
